{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":297574,"duration_api_ms":283217,"num_turns":64,"result":"The fix is complete. Here's a summary of the change:\n\n**Problem**: The modin 0.27.0 release was missing the `skipna` parameter in the `first` and `last` groupby methods. This parameter was added in pandas 2.2.3+ to align the API.\n\n**Solution**: Added the `skipna=True` parameter to both `first` and `last` methods in the `DataFrameGroupBy` class, and passed it through to the `agg_kwargs` dictionary so it gets forwarded to the underlying aggregation function.\n\n**Changes made**:\n- `modin/pandas/groupby.py`: Added `skipna=True` parameter to both `first()` and `last()` methods with default value `True` to match pandas 2.2.3+ API, and passed it through `agg_kwargs`.\n\nThis minimal fix ensures modin's `first` and `last` groupby methods accept the `skipna` parameter, aligning with the pandas API (FIX-#6968: Align API with pandas).","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"5ceaf6b6-f3ae-49a8-bc95-c3f87c6acd2a","total_cost_usd":3.19327485,"usage":{"input_tokens":970422,"cache_creation_input_tokens":579,"cache_read_input_tokens":248206,"output_tokens":10927,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"cache_deleted_input_tokens":0,"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed":{"inputTokens":983250,"outputTokens":11046,"cacheReadInputTokens":252212,"cacheCreationInputTokens":579,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":3.19327485,"contextWindow":196000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"a5528e29-ebf9-4cdc-b3ae-2e6686289e28"}
